                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1701: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-19T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 19, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 19—4:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>340. Your 118, April 13, 4 p.m., was repeated to Peck whom I urged if possible to
                    see Soong before his departure for Washington. This Peck was unfortunately
                    unable to do but he has replied as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 19, 9 a.m. My April 17, 11 a.m. Wang Ching-wei on April 18, 6
                            p.m., authorized me to telegraph you that he heartily approved claims
                            commission in principle and would send a formal reply as soon as
                            possible.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
